	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 30th 9:28 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Mages get Summon arrows at level 20. The arrows that are summoned are the only arrows in the game (thus far) that can hit creatures that are magic weapons only to hit. These arrows are also free, that's right...free. Some mages will sell, others offer for donation, but if you hook a mage up once with either some tanking or general adventuring, you can max you archery skill for free instead of actually buying ammo. <br><br>I'm in a guild with at least a 1/3rd of the members being rangers. Only three of my guildmates take advantage of my services, but they are all very happy about it. Last night, I was with two of these rangers and summoned over 700 arrows throughout the course of the evening. Both rangers raised there skill in archery by 25 points minimum. Plus, if you get loaded down, mages can summon 100% weight reducing bags, again for free.<br><br>So remember, we can't SoW (you can at 30) or port, but mages do have some nifty uses. So if any of you get True Shot and need some arrows, find a mage and make nice-nice.<br><br>Just my 2cp.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aaneldarie Tura'Seorsa<br>29th Season Magician&nbsp;&nbsp;Vazaelle</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
