<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98880596668891></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98880596668891><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=10&mid=98880596668891>RE: A archer's best companion...mages</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=10&mid=98880596668891#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17974><span id=Scholar>mpete</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>216 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 2nd 8:19 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes it's crazy expensive!!&nbsp;&nbsp;Even if you have a magic bow (trueshot, raincaller) you still must have a magic arrow.  This is silly.  I think if you have a magic bow you should be able to hit magic only creatures with regular arrows fired from that MAGIC bow!!  I love my archery and use it heavily when solo and to pull when grouped or solo but it needs some tweaking from Verant.  Im not holding my breath though.  If I were going into a situation which would require magic arrows I would much prefer a mage summon some rather than blowing tons of plats to make them.  Your fletching skill has to be pretty dam high as well before those magic arrows become trivial.    <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
