	   <tr><td colspan=2>Trueshot is a Lore item, but it is not magical.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notice how the Raincaller quest is about enchanting a Trueshot.  Also, "realistically" speaking, no, a magical bow shouldn't be able to hit creatures who require magical weapons to hit.  As far as gameplay, yes, it would be nice.<br>Think of it this way, undead (which account of what, 90 percent of creatures which require magical weapons to hit) aren't alive.  Nothing effects them the same way that it effects normal, living creatures.  If a zombie was to fall off of the empire state building, the impact would not effect it much, only magic can permanently beat down undead, since it is magic that "sustains" them.  And yes, I play a lot of D&D, hehe<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
